# Preferred agent skills

Always start domain/module work with the repo skill:

- `.cursor/skills/futrob-hexagonal-module/SKILL.md`

## Approved phase skills

Read and follow these when the task matches. Do not invent a parallel stack.

| Skill | When |
|---|---|
| **shadcn** (Vercel plugin / CLI) | Add or change primitives in `packages/ui`; compose in web presentation. Base UI only — see `ui-shadcn.mdc`. |
| **better-ui** | Visual pass on screens: hierarchy, density, empty/error states, operator vs spectator UI. |
| **gsap** (gsap-skills plugin) | Motion for landing, bracket zoom/pan presence, intentional transitions. Never in domain/application. Respect `prefers-reduced-motion`. |
| **layers-domain** | Clarify or rename domain concepts before coding (Encounter, OfficialMatch, Team, selection). |
| **layers-interaction-flow** | Captain selection, reschedule, sync → review → officialize flows before UI/API shape. |
| **web-perf** | SSR/Workers budgets, dense lists, bracket, public portal load. |
| **seo** | Public landing and competition portal metadata, crawlable published content only. |

## Platform skills (also expected)

- Cloudflare / wrangler / workers-best-practices for Workers, D1, R2, Queues, Cron
- Sentry at execution boundaries
- pstack typescript-best-practices for contracts and typed boundaries

## Local tooling

- `apps/cli` is the domain/use-case playground (fakes in memory). See `/apps/cli/README.md`.
- Product deployable remains `apps/web` only.

## Do not use for implementation here

Supabase, Railway deploy, Clerk, Convex, Nuxt, Astro, UnoCSS, Kapso/Chat SDK unless product direction explicitly reopens them.
